#- §lManifesto

§rMt. Augusta groans
under the weight of
it's own,
poorly-designed 
bureaucracy. Ever 
since the HCF invasion
destroyed it, it has never truly recovered.
Independence, however, will lead to
greatness.
#- §lA Declaration of Belief

§rOur Beliefs are diametrically opposed to those of the old regime.  Minarchism has proven its ineptitude time and time again.  In
response to this, we, the founders of New
Augusta, have decided to form a new
#- government, founded in efficency.  Our government is ultimately, in the name of efficiency, centralized.  We must not allow the grips of bureaucracy and over-complicated governmental structure to take hold upon the New Augustan state. We must use 
#-  common sense and dialogue to speak to each other and consult before making decisions

